      "body": "T8 diff audit (uncommitted, login-failed session) \u2014 VERDICT: SOUND & VERIFIED, with one signature-freeze note.\n\nAll 5 write-scope files were rebuilt by `lake build` (exit 0, 8564 jobs) \u2014 the failed session had built successfully and only failed at the login/commit gate; on-disk oleans content-match the working tree. Flagship closed lemma `Scheme.Modules.tensorObjRightUnitor_eq` is axiom-clean (propext/Classical.choice/Quot.sound; no sorryAx). No new sorry/admit/axiom/native_decide/implemented_by anywhere.\n\nPer file:\n- CechHigherDirectImage.lean: SOUND. 5 v4.31 sorries closed with real compiling proofs; only set_option reshuffling + bodies. Statements frozen.\n- SectionGradedRing.lean: SOUND (all 8 sorries genuinely closed and axiom-clean \u2014 contradicts the earlier 'HARD-BLOCKED by v4.31 monoidal API' pessimism; file is now sorry-free and builds). SEE NOTE below.\n- GlueDescent.lean: SOUND. 3 sorries closed; added @[reassoc] attrs + a set_option escape hatch. Statements frozen.\n- GrassmannianQuot.lean: SOUND. 2 substantial sorries closed (matrixEnd_pullback, matrixEndRect_pullback via cofan/row-sum) + small ones; several 'set_option backward.isDefEq.respectTransparency false in' shuffled off/onto proofs, all still compile. One cosmetic docstring rename ref (gr_pullbackObjUnitToUnit_comp -> pullbackObjUnitToUnit_comp).\n- QuotScheme.lean: SOUND. Exactly the 2 v4.31 sorries closed (isLocalizedModule_restrict_of_isIso_fromTilde\u0393 ~L1713, isIso_unitToPushforwardObjUnit_of_isIso' ~L2231); 12 structural stub sorries remain untouched (sanctioned).\n\nSIGNATURE-FREEZE NOTE (only deviation from T8's 'freeze ALL statements'): two PRIVATE helper lemmas in SectionGradedRing.lean had their statements reshaped:\n  1. tensorPowAdd_assoc_succ_core \u2014 removed hyps iab_CL, iABC_L (+ vars Q3,Q4), added hyp iT (+ Q11); goal equation reshaped.\n  2. tensorPowAdd_comm_succ_core \u2014 removed hyp itclm (+ Qtclm); goal reshaped.\nBoth are faithful algebraic rearrangements (cancelling adjacent iso hom/inv identity pairs / splitting a factor at a bridge iso), NOT weakenings \u2014 same coherence identity. Their public callers tensorPowAdd_assoc / tensorPowAdd_comm keep FROZEN signatures, were updated consistently (e.g. iT := ... passed at the call site), and prove sorry-free. Recommend reconcile bless these two helper reshapings (or restore original core shapes) rather than treat as blocking.\n\nNo stray files attributable to T8 (RationalCurveIso.{body,new,skeletal} at project root are baseline-registered since commit 180b985, not this session's output).",
